    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a matching lid (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong>&nbsp;vegetable oil</strong> over a low heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion</strong> with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until the onion has softened&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-pork-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>noodles</strong> to a pot of boiling water (enough to cover them) with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat</p> <p>Boil for 3 min or until starting to soften</p> <p>Meanwhile, trim the <strong>green beans</strong> and cut them in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-pork-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>green beans</strong> to the same pot as the&nbsp;<strong>noodles</strong> and cook for a further 3 min</p> <p>Once cooked, drain and rinse the lot briefly under cold water (to prevent them from sticking together and continuing to cook) before returning them to the pot (off the heat)</p> <p>Trim the fat off the<strong> pork steaks</strong>&nbsp;and slice finely into strips</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-pork-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pork strips</strong> to the <strong>onion pan</strong>, increase the heat to medium-high and cook for 4 min, then cover with a lid and cook for a further 2 min or until the pork has cooked through</p> <p>Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat and keep covered until later (this stops the pork overcooking)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-pork-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate (or finely chop) the <strong>ginger</strong></p> <p>Trim then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>finely</p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-pork-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>sesame oil</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 1 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]&nbsp;</span><strong>sugar</strong> and half the <strong>spring onion</strong> in a bowl - this is your <strong>chilli mixture</strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-pork-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pork&nbsp;to a medium-low heat, remove the lid, and add the <strong>chilli mixture</strong></p> <p>Cook for 1 min, then add the <strong>noodles</strong> (cut them up in the pan a little for easy eating)</p> <p>Remove from the heat and add the remaining <strong>spring onion</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-pork-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Taste for seasoning, adding salt and pepper if needed and serve</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
